s partially reduced to glutamate-5-semialdehyde, spontaneously cyclizes to P5C, and is reduced to proline. This pathway mirrors modern biosynthesis.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_018", "rxn_019", "rxn_020"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_016", "mol_017", "mol_018", "mol_020", "mol_022"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Proto-metabolic pathway via transamination with glycine", "description": "Variant of the proto-metabolic route where glutamate is formed by transamination between alpha-ketoglutarate and glycine (rather than reductive amination). Glycine is sourced from surface Strecker synthesis, demonstrating bidirectional environment coupling.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_007", "rxn_018", "rxn_019", "rxn_020"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_016", "mol_017", "mol_018", "mol_019", "mol_020", "mol_022"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "Full chain: hydrothermal CO\u2082 \u2192 glycine (Strecker) \u2192 transamination \u2192 proline", "description": "Complete multi-environment pathway: CO2 is fixed hydrothermally to formate \u2192 formaldehyde, transferred to surface for HCN synthesis and Strecker glycine synthesis. Glycine returns to hydrothermal environment for transamination with alpha-ketoglutarate to form glutamate, then proceeds through the P5C route to proline.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_008", "rxn_012", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_007", "rxn_018", "rxn_019", "rxn_020"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_005", "mol_019", "mol_018", "mol_020", "mol_022"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "Hydrothermal-to-surface HCN \u2192 Strecker 1-pyrroline route", "description": "Hydrothermal CO2 fixation provides formaldehyde, which is converted to HCN at the surface. Meanwhile, formaldehyde also generates glycolaldehyde and 4-aminobutanal. HCN adds to 1-pyrroline (formed from 4-aminobutanal) to give pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile, then hydrolysis yields proline. Both HCN and the C4 aldehyde derive from the same formaldehyde source.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_008", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_015", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_005", "mol_013", "mol_015", "mol_012"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "Direct alpha-ketoglutarate reductive amination to P5C route", "description": "Abbreviated proto-metabolic pathway starting from pyruvate and glyoxylate (assumed available from hydrothermal fixation). Aldol condensation yields alpha-ketoglutarate, reductive amination gives glutamate, then the P5C pathway yields proline. Emphasizes the minimal reaction network from C3+C2 alpha-keto acids.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_018", "rxn_019", "rxn_020"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_018", "mol_020", "mol_021", "mol_022"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Convergent surface cyanosulfidic + Strecker route via pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile", "description": "Demonstrates the convergence at pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile from two independent surface pathways: (a) the cyanosulfidic route through acrylonitrile and (b) the Strecker route through 1-pyrroline. Both feed into the same hydrolysis step to produce proline. This pathway highlights the network redundancy and robustness of prebiotic proline synthesis.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_011", "rxn_013", "rxn_014", "rxn_015", "rxn_016", "rxn_017"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_010", "mol_011", "mol_015", "mol_012"]}], "hub_molecules": ["mol_005", "mol_009", "mol_012", "mol_018", "mol_020"], "convergence_points": [{"molecule_id": "mol_005", "description": "Hydrogen cyanide (HCN) \u2014 primary C/N building block used across multiple pathways", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_008"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_012", "rxn_016"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_009", "description": "Formaldehyde \u2014 central C1 hub linking hydrothermal carbon fixation to surface chemistry", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_002"], "outgoing_reacti