: 0.88,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.80,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.77,\n            \"feedback\": \"Extends P1 with hydrothermal CO2 fixation origins, which is conceptually appealing and gives the full Hydrothermal \u2192 Surface \u2192 Biochemical flow. However, rxn_008 (formaldehyde + NH3 \u2192 HCN via UV dehydration) is the weakest link. HCN is typically formed from N2/NH3 + CH4 under high energy conditions (lightning, UV photolysis of CH4/N2 mixtures), not from formaldehyde dehydration with ammonia. Formaldehyde + NH3 more plausibly yields aminomethanol or formamide, not HCN directly.\",\n            \"approved\": false,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_002\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"Replace rxn_008 with a more established HCN production route, e.g., UV photolysis of formamide or atmospheric CH4+N2 chemistry\", \"rxn_002 formate to formaldehyde on magnetite needs stronger justification; consider using native iron or awaruite as catalyst\"]\n        },\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\n                \"rxn_013\": 0.72,\n                \"rxn_014\": 0.58,\n                \"rxn_015\": 0.85,\n                \"rxn_016\": 0.90,\n                \"rxn_017\": 0.78\n            },\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.73,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": 0.78,\n            \"environmental_progression\": 0.72,\n            \"target_achievement\": 0.82,\n            \"overall_confidence\": 0.76,\n            \"feedback\": \"The Strecker-like pathway through 4-aminobutanal and 1-pyrroline is a legitimate route discussed in the literature. The Strecker addition of HCN to 1-pyrroline (rxn_016) is well-established. However, rxn_014 is oversimplified\u2014the conversion of glycolaldehyde + formaldehyde + NH3 to 4-aminobutanal involves at least two distinct steps (aldol extension to a C4 aldehyde, then reductive amination), and the selectivity for the correct 