nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Proline\nOVERALL STRATEGY: Three primary prebiotically plausible routes converge on L-proline: (1) the Sutherland cyanosulfidic pathway via Cu(I)-catalyzed HCN/acetylene coupling to acrylonitrile, reductive homologation, cyclization, and hydrolysis; (2) the Strecker pathway through 1-pyrroline derived from glutamate decarboxylation/reduction; (3) the proto-metabolic hydrothermal pathway through alpha-ketoglutarate, glutamate, glutamate-5-semialdehyde, and P5C reduction. Hub molecules (HCN, pyruvate, alpha-ketoglutarate, pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile, P5C) create convergence points across environments. Chiral enrichment is achieved via proline-mediated asymmetric catalysis on calcite surfaces, as documented by Blackmond and coworkers.\n\nMOLECULES (26 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_006: C2H2 (acetylene) [starting]\n  - mol_007: CHOO- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: CH2O (formaldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H4O3 (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H2O3 (glyoxylate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C5H6O5 (alpha-ketoglutarate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H9NO4 (glutamate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C5H9NO3 (glutamate-5-semialdehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H7NO3 (delta-1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate (P5C)) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H3N (acrylonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C5H7N3 (2-aminopentanedinitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C5H8N2 (pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_018: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_019: C4H9NO2 (gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA)) [intermediate]\n  - mol_020: C4H9NO (4-aminobutanal) [intermediate