nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Proline\nOVERALL STRATEGY: Multi-environment synthesis network for L-proline integrating three established paradigms: (1) Sutherland cyanosulfidic photoredox chemistry producing pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile via reductive homologation of HCN and acetylene; (2) proto-metabolic hydrothermal r-TCA cycle analog producing alpha-ketoglutarate, then glutamate, glutamate-5-semialdehyde, and P5C following the biological biosynthetic logic (Stubbs & Moran); (3) Strecker-type chemistry via 1-pyrroline intermediate. Hub molecules (HCN, pyruvate, alpha-ketoglutarate, pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile, P5C) create convergence points. Glutamate-5-semialdehyde serves as a critical branch point feeding both the P5C reduction route and the Strecker route via thermal decarboxylation to 4-aminobutanal. Chiral enrichment via calcite-mediated differential adsorption and proline-catalyzed amplification (Blackmond). Environmental flow: Hydrothermal CO2 fixation \u2192 Surface cyanosulfidic/Strecker chemistry \u2192 Biochemical assembly and chiral selection.\n\nMOLECULES (25 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_006: C2H2 (acetylene) [starting]\n  - mol_007: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_008: CHO2- (formate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: CH2O (formaldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H2O3 (glyoxylate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H6O5 (alpha-ketoglutarate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H9NO4 (glutamate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C5H9NO3 (glutamate-5-semialdehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C5H7NO3 (delta-1-pyrroline-5-carbo